A case of concealment of birth has been opened by the Alexandra Road police after an infant was found dumped in a bin in Aloe ridge, Pietermaritzburg, on Friday. According to spokesperson Colonel Kholeka Mhlongo, the infant was found by an unknown individual who claimed to have been cleaning in Aloe Ridge. “The cleaner said he came across a bin with a Woolworths plastic bag inside and on searching it, found an infant,” said Mhlongo. He added that the man then alerted the nearest security guards who then alerted the police about the incident. The infant was already dead when it was found.